texts.text: >--X years ago--
>The Pixie from another dimension flutters unsteadily down the mountain.
...I hope that human's alright...
That human had the face of someone who's about to die...
>Pixie looks back at whence she came. There's no one there.
What am I thinking. There's no reason for that human to come looking for me.
I'm all alone again, with no clue at all how to get back home.
Alone in a strange world...
>Pixie looks back again. Still no one.
What should I do now...
All I want to do is go home...
Grrrr...

Whoa?!
W-Who's there?!
Grrrr...
Oh... Ummm, wait. I...
Garrr!!
Eeek!
>The beastly demon sends Pixie flying with a single blow!
G-Gotta escape...!
*Roar*
Pixie flutters feebly away to escape, but the demon gives chase...!
Garrr!
Eeek!

*Pant*
N-No... Can't move... Too exhausted...
>Wavering, Pixie drops to the ground.
>The beastlike demon moves in on her...
This... This is so unfair...
(I don't even know anyone in this world...)
>The demon's fangs are inches away from Pixie, but she is too weak to move.
(So I'm going to die here, all alone...)
*Whimper*
(...That's odd. What's that human doing here...?)
>The last thing Pixie sees before passing out is
>the beastlike demon being driven away, and the worried face of a human.

...
*Groan*
>Pixies wakes up to the faint light and crackling sounds of a fire.
I-I'm... alive.
You're awake.
You okay?
Huh...? Oh, yeah. Wait, you're that human from before...
You saved me again. Why?
>After pausing for a second to contemplate the answer,
>you say you don't know.
You don't know...?
Okay, then why are you in a place like this alone?
Don't you have friends and family? A... home?
>You look into Pixie's questioning eyes,
>and you shake your head.
I lost everything.
I have nothing left.
Everything? What do you mean?
You have no one? Not even a home?
Nothing left... Okay...
Not even a single thing?
>You answer Pixie's question with a faraway look in your eye,
>saying you have nothing left.
>No home, no companions, no goals and no hope.
>You tell her you lost them all.
(What a sad person...)
...Hey.
Hello?!
You all alone mister?
You all alone miss?
Then I can stay with you if you want.
>You see Pixie teetering in the air.
>She talks loud enough, but she's so weak it feels like she'd vanish from existence at any moment.
>It takes you a moment to realize that tears are streaming down your face.
Oh good, you still remember how to cry.
...It's okay. I cried yesterday, now it's your turn.
>Pixie holds up the end of her sash and wipes away your tears.
>You were unable to save the world. You thought it was all over.
>...But now you realize what you call the world is not just the planet you live on,
>it is made out of every living organism inhabiting it.
>Looking at Pixie, it all becomes so clear to you.

...?
W-What? Why're you looking at me like that?
>Trapped in an unknown world and unable to find a way back, the tiny thing in front of you
>is bruised and battered, so feeble that she might vanish from existence at any time.
>...I can't forsake this sad little thing.
>...I can't forsake this sad little thing.
Partners then.
We can travel together.
Oh. Ummm... okay.
I mean, I can't just leave you on your own.
You're probably very lonely cuz you lost everything...
But have no fear, I'm with you now. You don't have to feel lonely anymore.
>You decide to stick around in this world just a bit longer, if only to see how this little demon's story ends.
>The world may not have much time left,
>but you hope she gets a happy ending...
>--Present day---
>The intense battle with the strangely obsessed Unicorn
>is drawing to a close, you can feel it in your gut.
Brr... Gaaaaaa!!
Yaaaaa!!
